PyDoc_STRVAR(__pyx_doc_9mespprc_c_18instance_generator_2calibrate_instance, "\n    Calibrate resource limits until the current route pool supports a full-cover solution.\n\n    Calibration is intentionally separate from generation and from benchmarking. It keeps\n    all arc values fixed and only relaxes limits when needed:\n    1. Phase 1 route support is checked under the current local limits.\n    2. Phase 2 is checked without global limits to detect local infeasibility.\n    3. Phase 2 is checked with global limits to detect duty-time infeasibility.\n\n    The final returned instance is the one intended for timed DP vs IP benchmarks.\n    ");
